Package context.arch.intelligibility.expression


Interface Summary
Expression To represent an explanation expression that can be structured into a tree structure, that can be reformed into Disjunctive Normal Form.
 

Class Summary
ComparableRange<T extends Comparable<? super T>> Continuous range that can specify whether the bounds are inclusive or exclusive.
Comparison<T extends Comparable<? super T>> This only deals with numeric values that can be subjected to inequalities.
Conjunction<E extends Expression> List of expressions as an AND combination.
Disjunction<E extends Expression> List of expressions as an OR combination.
DNF Convenience class to represent a Disjunction of Expressions taking the Disjunctive Normal Form (DNF).
Negated<T extends Comparable<? super T>> This is meant to be a terminal Negation, i.e.
Negation Expression representing the boolean NOT operation on an expression.
Parameter<T extends Comparable<? super T>> An Expression representing name=Value.
Reason Convenience class to represent a single reason, or reason trace.
Unknown Represents that the explanation is unknown.
